This paper is about computational cognitive modeling, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the use of Constraint Handling Rules (CHR) to reason about computational properties of ACT-R models, which falls under the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with the implementation of rules and strategies, which is related to programming languages (cs.PL). The topic of cognitive processes also has a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper discusses the use of invariants, which is a topic in cybernetics (cs.CY).
